KZN cops have recovered a stolen cow that was used to pay lobola. On Tuesday, the Zululand Multi-District Stock Theft Task Team followed a tip-off regarding the livestock stolen at Gluckstadt Village over the weekend. ALSO READ: CIT HEIST GUARDS BUST! Captain Nqobile Gwala said they went to the Makhukhula area where a stray cow was found. “The cow was positively identified by the owner as the one that was stolen over the weekend. “The team proceeded to another homestead where cattle and a calf were found at the same area,” Captain Gwala said. Gwala said their investigations revealed that the cattle was brought in March 2019 to the homestead as lobola for their daughter. “The cow and two-month-old calf were seized by police and were positively identified by the lawful owner. Investigations are still ongoing,” Captain Gwala added.